Paul Crowley (pdc@dcs.ed.ac.uk) wrote:
> Do we have a clear definition of the complexity class (QP?) that
> factoring has been found to be in?  Since, I'm told, it's suspected
> that QP!=NP.  Do we know what quantum computers would be like well
> enough to describe an abstract machine with the same power,

Yes


> and if so,
> what's that machine like?

Like a quantum computer.

There is no classical description capable of describing a quantum
computer.  A quantum computer has to be described in terms of
Hilbert space.

No intellectual short cuts are available.  No royal road.

